#. <section class="sutta" id="mn71"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn71:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 71"
msgstr "Middle Discourses 71"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn71:0.2"
msgid "Tevijjavacchasutta"
msgstr "To Vacchagotta on the Three Knowledges"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya1"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "mn71:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "mn71:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the "
"hall with the peaked roof."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya2"></a>
msgctxt "mn71:2.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena vacchagotto paribbājako ekapuṇḍarīke paribbājakārāme "
"paṭivasati."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time the wanderer Vacchagotta was residing in the Single Lotus "
"Monastery of the wanderers."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya3"></a>
msgctxt "mn71:3.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya vesāliṃ piṇḍāya "
"pāvisi."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, "
"entered Vesālī for alms."

msgctxt "mn71:3.2"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavato etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then it occurred to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "mn71:3.3"
msgid "“atippago kho tāva vesāliyaṃ piṇḍāya carituṃ;"
msgstr "“It’s too early to wander for alms in Vesālī."

msgctxt "mn71:3.4"
msgid ""
"yannūnāhaṃ yena ekapuṇḍarīko paribbājakārāmo yena vacchagotto paribbājako "
"tenupasaṅkameyyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"Why don’t I visit the wanderer Vacchagotta at the Single Lotus Monastery?”"

msgctxt "mn71:3.5"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā yena ekapuṇḍarīko paribbājakārāmo yena vacchagotto "
"paribbājako tenupasaṅkami."
msgstr "So that’s what he did."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya4"></a>
msgctxt "mn71:4.1"
msgid "Addasā kho vacchagotto paribbājako bhagavantaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ."
msgstr "Vacchagotta saw the Buddha coming off in the distance,"

msgctxt "mn71:4.2"
msgid "Disvāna bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "and said to him:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.482"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "mn71:4.3"
msgid "“Etu kho, bhante, bhagavā."
msgstr "“Come, Blessed One!"

msgctxt "mn71:4.4"
msgid "Svāgataṃ, bhante, bhagavato."
msgstr "Welcome, Blessed One!"

msgctxt "mn71:4.5"
msgid "Cirassaṃ kho, bhante, bhagavā imaṃ pariyāyamakāsi yadidaṃ idhāgamanāya."
msgstr "It’s been a long time since you took the opportunity to come here."

msgctxt "mn71:4.6"
msgid "Nisīdatu, bhante, bhagavā idamāsanaṃ paññattan”ti."
msgstr "Please, sir, sit down, this seat is ready.”"

msgctxt "mn71:4.7"
msgid "Nisīdi bhagavā paññatte āsane."
msgstr "The Buddha sat on the seat spread out,"

msgctxt "mn71:4.8"
msgid ""
"Vacchagottopi kho paribbājako aññataraṃ nīcaṃ āsanaṃ gahetvā ekamantaṃ "
"nisīdi."
msgstr "while Vacchagotta took a low seat and sat to one side."

msgctxt "mn71:4.9"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho vacchagotto paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then Vacchagotta said to the Buddha:"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya5"></a>
msgctxt "mn71:5.1"
msgid "“sutaṃ metaṃ, bhante:"
msgstr "“Sir, I have heard this:"

msgctxt "mn71:5.2"
msgid ""
"‘samaṇo gotamo sabbaññū sabbadassāvī, aparisesaṃ ñāṇadassanaṃ paṭijānāti, "
msgstr ""
"‘The ascetic Gotama claims to be all-knowing and all-seeing, to know and see "
"everything without exception, thus: "

msgctxt "mn71:5.3"
msgid ""
"carato ca me tiṭṭhato ca suttassa ca jāgarassa ca satataṃ samitaṃ "
"ñāṇadassanaṃ paccupaṭṭhitan’ti."
msgstr ""
"“Knowledge and vision are constantly and continually present to me, while "
"walking, standing, sleeping, and waking.”’"

msgctxt "mn71:5.4"
msgid ""
"Ye te, bhante, evamāhaṃsu: ‘samaṇo gotamo sabbaññū sabbadassāvī, aparisesaṃ "
"ñāṇadassanaṃ paṭijānāti, carato ca me tiṭṭhato ca suttassa ca jāgarassa ca "
"satataṃ samitaṃ ñāṇadassanaṃ paccupaṭṭhitan’ti, kacci te, bhante, bhagavato "
"vuttavādino, na ca bhagavantaṃ abhūtena abbhācikkhanti, dhammassa "
"cānudhammaṃ byākaronti, na ca koci sahadhammiko vādānuvādo gārayhaṃ ṭhānaṃ "
"āgacchatī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"I trust that those who say this repeat what the Buddha has said, and do not "
"misrepresent him with an untruth? Is their explanation in line with the "
"teaching? Are there any legitimate grounds for rebuke and criticism?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "mn71:5.5"
msgid ""
"“Ye te, vaccha, evamāhaṃsu: ‘samaṇo gotamo sabbaññū sabbadassāvī, aparisesaṃ "
"ñāṇadassanaṃ paṭijānāti, carato ca me tiṭṭhato ca suttassa ca jāgarassa ca "
"satataṃ samitaṃ ñāṇadassanaṃ paccupaṭṭhitan’ti, na me te vuttavādino, "
"abbhācikkhanti ca pana maṃ asatā abhūtenā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Vaccha, those who say this do not repeat what I have said. They "
"misrepresent me with what is false and untrue.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya6"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "mn71:6.1"
msgid ""
"“Kathaṃ byākaramānā pana mayaṃ, bhante, vuttavādino ceva bhagavato assāma, "
"na ca bhagavantaṃ abhūtena abbhācikkheyyāma, dhammassa cānudhammaṃ "
"byākareyyāma, na ca koci sahadhammiko vādānuvādo gārayhaṃ ṭhānaṃ "
"āgaccheyyā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“So how should we answer so as to repeat what the Buddha has said, and not "
"misrepresent him with an untruth? How should we explain in line with his "
"teaching, with no legitimate grounds for rebuke and criticism?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "mn71:6.2"
msgid ""
"“‘Tevijjo samaṇo gotamo’ti kho, vaccha, byākaramāno vuttavādī ceva me assa, "
"na ca maṃ abhūtena abbhācikkheyya, dhammassa cānudhammaṃ byākareyya, na ca "
"koci sahadhammiko vādānuvādo gārayhaṃ ṭhānaṃ āgaccheyya."
msgstr ""
"“‘The ascetic Gotama has the three knowledges.’ Answering like this you "
"would repeat what I have said, and not misrepresent me with an untruth. You "
"would explain in line with my teaching, and there would be no legitimate "
"grounds for rebuke and criticism."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya7"></a>
msgctxt "mn71:7.1"
msgid ""
"Ahañhi, vaccha, yāvadeva ākaṅkhāmi anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarāmi,"
msgstr "For, Vaccha, whenever I want, I recollect my many kinds of past lives."

msgctxt "mn71:7.2"
msgid ""
"seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ dvepi jātiyo … pe … iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ "
"anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarāmi."
msgstr ""
"That is: one, two, three, four, five, ten, twenty, thirty, forty, fifty, a "
"hundred, a thousand, a hundred thousand rebirths; many eons of the world "
"contracting, many eons of the world evolving, many eons of the world "
"contracting and evolving. I remember: ‘There, I was named this, my clan was "
"that, I looked like this, and that was my food. This was how I felt pleasure "
"and pain, and that was how my life ended. When I passed away from that place "
"I was reborn somewhere else. There, too, I was named this, my clan was that, "
"I looked like this, and that was my food. This was how I felt pleasure and "
"pain, and that was how my life ended. When I passed away from that place I "
"was reborn here.’ And so I recollect my many kinds of past lives, with "
"features and details."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya8"></a>
msgctxt "mn71:8.1"
msgid ""
"Ahañhi, vaccha, yāvadeva ākaṅkhāmi dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena "
"atikkantamānusakena satte passāmi cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe "
"dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate … pe … yathākammūpage satte pajānāmi."
msgstr ""
"And whenever I want, with clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, I "
"see sentient beings passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, "
"beautiful and ugly, in a good place or a bad place. I understand how "
"sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya9"></a>
msgctxt "mn71:9.1"
msgid ""
"Ahañhi, vaccha, āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva "
"dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmi."
msgstr ""
"And I have realized the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in "
"this very life. I live having realized it with my own insight due to the "
"ending of defilements."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya10"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.483"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "mn71:10.1"
msgid ""
"‘Tevijjo samaṇo gotamo’ti kho, vaccha, byākaramāno vuttavādī ceva me assa, "
"na ca maṃ abhūtena abbhācikkheyya, dhammassa cānudhammaṃ byākareyya, na ca "
"koci sahadhammiko vādānuvādo gārayhaṃ ṭhānaṃ āgaccheyyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘The ascetic Gotama has the three knowledges.’ Answering like this you would "
"repeat what I have said, and not misrepresent me with an untruth. You would "
"explain in line with my teaching, and there would be no legitimate grounds "
"for rebuke and criticism.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya11"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "mn71:11.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, vacchagotto paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he said this, the wanderer Vacchagotta said to the Buddha:"

# Note that while BB translates as if a pp, hence referring to historical fact, the text itself is phrased as an abstract question.
msgctxt "mn71:11.2"
msgid ""
"“atthi nu kho, bho gotama, koci gihī gihisaṃyojanaṃ appahāya kāyassa bhedā "
"dukkhassantakaro”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Master Gotama, are there any laypeople who, without giving up the fetter of "
"lay life, make an end of suffering when the body breaks up?”"

msgctxt "mn71:11.3"
msgid ""
"“Natthi kho, vaccha, koci gihī gihisaṃyojanaṃ appahāya kāyassa bhedā "
"dukkhassantakaro”ti."
msgstr "“No, Vaccha.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya12"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "mn71:12.1"
msgid ""
"“Atthi pana, bho gotama, koci gihī gihisaṃyojanaṃ appahāya kāyassa bhedā "
"saggūpago”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But are there any laypeople who, without giving up the fetter of lay life, "
"go to heaven when the body breaks up?”"

#. VAR: atha kho → atthi kho
msgctxt "mn71:12.2"
msgid ""
"“Na kho, vaccha, ekaṃyeva sataṃ na dve satāni na tīṇi satāni na cattāri "
"satāni na pañca satāni, atha kho bhiyyova ye gihī gihisaṃyojanaṃ appahāya "
"kāyassa bhedā saggūpagā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“There’s not just one hundred laypeople, Vaccha, or two or three or four or "
"five hundred, but many more than that who, without giving up the fetter of "
"lay life, go to heaven when the body breaks up.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya13"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
#. VAR: ājīvako → ājīviko (mr)
msgctxt "mn71:13.1"
msgid ""
"“Atthi nu kho, bho gotama, koci ājīvako kāyassa bhedā dukkhassantakaro”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Master Gotama, are there any <i>Ājīvaka</i> ascetics who make an end of "
"suffering when the body breaks up?”"

msgctxt "mn71:13.2"
msgid "“Natthi kho, vaccha, koci ājīvako kāyassa bhedā dukkhassantakaro”ti."
msgstr "“No, Vaccha.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya14"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "mn71:14.1"
msgid "“Atthi pana, bho gotama, koci ājīvako kāyassa bhedā saggūpago”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But are there any <i>Ājīvaka</i> ascetics who go to heaven when the body "
"breaks up?”"

#. VAR: kho so, vaccha, ekanavuto kappo → ito kho vaccha ekanavute kappe (mr)
msgctxt "mn71:14.2"
msgid ""
"“Ito kho so, vaccha, ekanavuto kappo yamahaṃ anussarāmi, nābhijānāmi kañci "
"ājīvakaṃ saggūpagaṃ aññatra ekena;"
msgstr ""
"“Vaccha, when I recollect the past ninety-one eons, I can’t find any "
"<i>Ājīvaka</i> ascetics who have gone to heaven, except one;"

msgctxt "mn71:14.3"
msgid "sopāsi kammavādī kiriyavādī”ti."
msgstr "and he taught the efficacy of deeds and action.”"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya15"></a>
msgctxt "mn71:15.1"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ sante, bho gotama, suññaṃ aduṃ titthāyatanaṃ antamaso saggūpagenapī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“In that case, Master Gotama, the sectarian tenets are empty even of the "
"chance to go to heaven.”"

msgctxt "mn71:15.2"
msgid "“Evaṃ, vaccha, suññaṃ aduṃ titthāyatanaṃ antamaso saggūpagenapī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Yes, Vaccha, the sectarian tenets are empty even of the chance to go to "
"heaven.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "mn71:15.3"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "mn71:15.4"
msgid "Attamano vacchagotto paribbājako bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti."
msgstr ""
"Satisfied, the wanderer Vacchagotta was happy with what the Buddha said."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn71:15.5"
msgid "Tevijjavacchasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
